	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I hated school when studying subjects that didn't interest me but liked it a lot when the subjects were cool. Work is kind of the same thing for me, but more often than not I have to do things I don't enjoy at all. When I'm employed I hardly ever have any free time, since overtime, commuting and taking care of my daughter and home takes away what would otherwise count as free time. When working from home things are a little better, specially if I get to pick the kind of work I'll do.<br /><br />So, if I had to pick one, school was better than work, I guess.<br /><br />My spare time goes mostly to programming and drawing. I also enjoy going out with family and friends.

		

		</td>
